<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Memoize the result of each visit so that we only compute once for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the same input SCEV. This is to avoid redundant computations when</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a SCEV is referenced by multiple SCEVs. Without memoization, this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// visit algorithm would have exponential time complexity in the worst</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// case, causing the compiler to hang on certain tests.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scevrewritevisitor/#a8d3df2fe9a155fd1bc46630a3be5f0ae"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smalldensemap">SmallDenseMap&lt;const SCEV &#42;, const SCEV &#42;&gt;</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scevrewritevisitor/#a8d3df2fe9a155fd1bc46630a3be5f0ae">RewriteResults</a>;</span></CodeLine>
